      <description>&lt;p&gt;Functional random values, or a sequence of well-spread values.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Did some evening Clojuring with a bunch of my padawans and friends. Everything looked goodâ€”free of side effects, single state, masteryâ€”until randomness suddenly appeared as a hidden input.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;I quickly recommended passing randomness explicitly as input, perhaps stored in the single state and continuously transformed. This way, randomness becomes side-effect free and repeatable. The next random value is simply a deterministic transformation of the previous one.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
